Date: 96-25, 1996,  
Abstract: This paper presents a selection procedure that combines Bechhofer's indifference zone selection and Gupta's subset selection approaches, by using a preference threshold. A subset of populations is selected that have sample sums within the distance of this threshold from the largest sample sum. Aiming at designing the experiment, we derive the minimal necessary sample size and the value for the preference threshold, in order to satisfy two requirements for correct selection. One requirement is related to the indifference zone method, the other to the subset selection method. Considered are normal populations with common known variance and several properties of the procedure are presented. The method is further discussed using simulation studies. 
